track_notes:
From El Paso, trave 110 miles east on US Hwy 62/180. Turn in to the Guadalupe Mountains HQ and Visitors Center. Take the first left to the Pine Springs Campground. The trail-head is in the left-rear of the parking area. Pay your park fees and gather your gear.

The trail is well marked, so just read the signs.  The first 1.5 miles is a steep climb out of the desert floor. Once you get over the ridge-line, the trail crosses over into an alpine-forest region. The trail will switch-back up and west until you climb out of the forest and out in the bare rock upper region.  There is nothing really difficult about the trail until the very last scramble to reach the summit.  The actual summit is a broad dome-like region with a few low shrubs and some rocks worthy of sitting on.
The trail is very well maintained.  highly recommend this hike!
